## 5️⃣ API / INTEGRATION LAYER

### Current API Status
**Gibbon v31 includes NO REST API by default**  
- Traditional PHP page-based architecture
- Form submissions via POST
- AJAX endpoints for specific features

### Required: Create REST API Layer

#### API Endpoints Needed

**1. Authentication API**
```
POST /api/auth/login
POST /api/auth/logout
POST /api/auth/refresh
GET  /api/auth/check
```

**2. Student Data API**
```
GET  /api/students                    # List students
GET  /api/students/{id}               # Student details
GET  /api/students/{id}/profile       # Full profile
GET  /api/students/{id}/classes       # Enrolled classes
GET  /api/students/{id}/grades        # Academic records
```

**3. Attendance API**
```
POST /api/attendance/mark             # Take attendance
GET  /api/attendance/student/{id}     # Student history
GET  /api/attendance/class/{id}       # Class attendance
GET  /api/attendance/report          # Summary reports
```

**4. Course/Class API**
```
GET  /api/courses                     # List courses
GET  /api/courses/{id}                # Course details
GET  /api/classes/{id}                # Class details
GET  /api/timetable/{id}              # User timetable
```

#### Implementation Approach

**Option A: Add REST API Module** (RECOMMENDED)
Create: `/modules/REST API/`

Structure:
```
modules/REST API/
├── api.php                  # Main router
├── controllers/
│   ├── AuthController.php
│   ├── StudentController.php
│   ├── AttendanceController.php
│   └── CourseController.php
├── middleware/
│   ├── JWTAuth.php
│   └── CORS.php
└── routes.php
```

**Option B: Use Existing Slim Framework**
Gibbon already includes Slim 4.0 - leverage it:

Create: `/api/index.php`
```php
<?php
use Slim\Factory\AppFactory;
use Psr\Http\Message\ResponseInterface as Response;
use Psr\Http\Message\ServerRequestInterface as Request;

require __DIR__ . '/../vendor/autoload.php';
require __DIR__ . '/../config.php';

$app = AppFactory::create();

// Authentication endpoint
$app->post('/auth/login', function (Request $request, Response $response) {
    // Implementation
});

$app->run();
```

#### Authentication Strategy

**JWT-based Authentication** (RECOMMENDED)
1. Login returns JWT token
2. Token includes user ID, role, expiry
3. Frontend stores token (localStorage/cookie)
4. Each API request includes token in header
5. Backend validates token + checks Gibbon session

**Implementation:**
```php
use Firebase\JWT\JWT;
use Firebase\JWT\Key;

// Generate token on login
$payload = [
    'user_id' => $userId,
    'role' => $userRole,
    'exp' => time() + 3600  // 1 hour
];
$jwt = JWT::encode($payload, $jwtSecret, 'HS256');

// Validate token on requests
try {
    $decoded = JWT::decode($token, new Key($jwtSecret, 'HS256'));
    // Authorized
} catch (Exception $e) {
    // Unauthorized
}
```

