## 6️⃣ FRONTEND INTEGRATION

### Your Current Frontend
You have a React-based frontend at:
- `/media/swastik/focus/ldm new updae 2.0/ldm_test/`
- Already has login pages, dashboards, etc.

### Integration Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────┐
│   React Frontend    │
│  (ldmcollege.com)   │
└──────────┬──────────┘
           │ API Calls (HTTPS)
           ▼
┌─────────────────────┐
│    API Layer        │
│ (ldmcollege.com/api)│
└──────────┬──────────┘
           │
           ▼
┌─────────────────────┐
│  Gibbon Backend     │
│ (Internal PHP/MySQL)│
└─────────────────────┘
```

### API Integration Examples

#### Login Flow
```typescript
// Frontend: Login.tsx
const handleLogin = async (username: string, password: string) => {
  try {
    const response = await fetch('https://ldmcollege.com/api/auth/login', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ username, password })
    });
    
    const data = await response.json();
    
    if (data.success) {
      // Store JWT token
      localStorage.setItem('authToken', data.token);
      localStorage.setItem('userRole', data.role);
      
      // Redirect based on role
      if (data.role === 'student') {
        navigate('/student/dashboard');
      } else if (data.role === 'teacher') {
        navigate('/teacher/dashboard');
      } else if (data.role === 'admin') {
        navigate('/admin/dashboard');
      }
    }
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Login failed:', error);
  }
};
```

#### Fetch Student Data
```typescript
// Frontend: StudentDashboard.tsx
const fetchStudentData = async (studentId: string) => {
  const token = localStorage.getItem('authToken');
  
  const response = await fetch(`https://ldmcollege.com/api/students/${studentId}`, {
    headers: {
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`,
      'Content-Type': 'application/json'
    }
  });
  
  const data = await response.json();
  return data;
};
```

#### Take Attendance
```typescript
// Frontend: AttendanceComponent.tsx
const markAttendance = async (classId: string, attendanceData: any[]) => {
  const token = localStorage.getItem('authToken');
  
  const response = await fetch('https://ldmcollege.com/api/attendance/mark', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`,
      'Content-Type': 'application/json'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      classId,
      date: new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],
      attendance: attendanceData
    })
  });
  
  return response.json();
};
```

### Secure Data Fetching
Create a centralized API utility:

```typescript
// src/utils/api.ts
const API_BASE = 'https://ldmcollege.com/api';

export const api = {
  get: async (endpoint: string) => {
    const token = localStorage.getItem('authToken');
    const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE}${endpoint}`, {
      headers: {
        'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`,
        'Content-Type': 'application/json'
      }
    });
    return response.json();
  },
  
  post: async (endpoint: string, data: any) => {
    const token = localStorage.getItem('authToken');
    const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE}${endpoint}`, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`,
        'Content-Type': 'application/json'
      },
      body: JSON.stringify(data)
    });
    return response.json();
  }
};
```

